Product name: Star Wars Deluxe Probe Droid With Proton Torpedo and Self-Destruct Exploding Head, Power of the Force
Description:
"An Imperial probe droid."
    "It's a good bet the Empire knows we're here." 
    ―Princess Leia Organa and Han Solo
The Imperial probe droid was specially designed for deep space reconnaissance. Tenacious hunters and searchers, probe droids were equipped with a variety of sensors, and the ones employed by the Empire were armed with powerful blasters. Upon arrival at their target destination, they gather information and transmit it back to the Empire. If their mission is compromised, these droids can self-destruct. 
The Imperial probes are creepy looking as they slither and skitter along the surface of a planet on their spindly articulated legs. You know you are in trouble if their bulbous sensor "eyes" detect you.
This vintage Star War Probe Droid probe is in played in condition. The proton torpedo still fires and the head still self-destructs. Release date: 1996
May the force be with you!

Product name: Vintage The Bay - Hudson's Bay Company - Loop Collar Shirt - Medium
Description:
ABOUT THIS SHIRT
Very few clothing brands can boast a heritage dating back to 1670!  The Hudson's Bay Company (HBC) has its origins in the trapping and fur trade, when the virgin territories of the new world was the focus of the colonial machinations of the old.. ‘The Bay’ is one of the trading names of HBC with the Blue Ribbon label being introduced in 1966 following a re-branding to this visual identity in 1965. The label is not so much of a brand but rather a stamp of approval that was intended for use by non-Company Men’s brand garment items. At the time it was the policy of the Company to attach an approved Company identifier on merchandise where the quality of such merchandise would reflect favourably on or even enhance the reputation of the Company.
Features
*  4 inch convertible loop collar;
*  Double button cuff;
*  Polycotton fabric;
*  Loop collar shirt;
*  Original buttons.
Sizing (approximate in inches)
Vintage garments can change shape over time due to washing and general wear and tear. This means that a size large shirt may fit like a medium. I will include label information when available, but also add my own measurements, though these should be considered as ‘approximate’
Label: 'Medium'
Neck: 15.5
Shoulder (top of sleeve to top of sleeve): 17.5
Underarm to underarm: 20
Length (top of collar roll to hem): 32
Condition
This shirt is new without tags and has never been worn. Overall condition is great and there are no holes, rips or stains
This shirt comes neatly folded and READY to WEAR.
Shipping
I use the Royal Mail 1st Class 'Track & Signed For' service when shipping items. I do not always weigh or measure items before listing them, however, whatever shipping costs I quote are a maximum and include packaging. If shipping costs turn out to be significantly less than than the amount paid to me by customers, I will always reimburse the difference.

Description:
Marble mazes are a perfect sensory game. They are fun for children and adults! A simple but very effective way to keep hands active. A marble has been sewn between two layers of fabric, and a path stitched (tripled stitched for strength and durability) into a maze pattern. The object of the game is to push the marble through the maze path.
This activity encourages
-focus and patience 
-hand/eye co-ordination 
-fine motor skills
-problem solving
Marble mazes are an excellent game to use with children on the spectrum, hand therapy patients, those with Alzheimer's and dementia, those with arthritic hands etc. It is a great quiet time activity that easily fits in your handbag which makes it perfect to pull out at church, the doctor's surgery, restaurants and car rides. 
The marble maze is approx. 17cm x 23cm. One side is a fun, colourful pattern and the other side is a textured fabric - soft minky.
Please choose the pattern/colour you would like in the pull down section when ordering or contact me about a custom fabric choice. 
Items will ship within 3-5 days of receipt of payment. Please refer to my shop policies for questions regarding shipping.
Cleaning instructions: To clean your marble maze simply throw it in the washing machine and let it air dry.

(If we do not receive a reply within 48 hours on the draft design then we will go ahead and make the order so as not to delay). From then I would allow around 4 working days for it to be made (normally sooner) before being shipped.
► Your Image (if you are personalising using photos):
- We recommend that for best results each image should have up to 2 people only present and due to the small size that they are close together. The glass does magnify the image slightly so both will therefore easily be seen. 
- The closer everyone is in the image, generally the better the results. If you are unsure if your image would work then please message me and I can advise you from there.
- Ensure that you hold the copyright to the pictures that are being uploaded, professional photographs should be only used if you have spoken to the photographer and obtained permission first.
► Size & Material :
• Silver plated cufflink settings, glass domes, sealant and personalised text/image prints
• Size of the image within the cufflinks is 16mm in diameter
• The cufflinks are water-resistant but not waterproof so avoid submerging into water
► Production Time:
• Normally it takes around 2 working days to receive a mockup or proof of your design via an Etsy message
• After agreeing the proof it can take up to 5 working days after this for me to hand-make the item 
• Please always check the announcements section at the top of my store for up-to-date wait times since everything is made to order and busy times such as Christmas can slightly alter this. If you need it sooner then message me and I will see what I can do for you
• During busy periods this can take longer but will state an up-to-date estimate in the Announcements section at the top of my Etsy shop
..............................
How to Order a Personalised Item:
1. Purchase the item using the 'add to cart' function as normal, remember to use the drop down to choose whether you would like any photos to be in colour or black & white if they are used
2. Leave a note in the msg box or message me on Etsy when you check out with your clear personalisation details so we know what to add as text on each cufflink if text is required
You can send us any pictures via a conversation message here on Etsy after ordering
3. If you are unsure about anything please ask us first and we will be happy to help
..............................
► Shipping & Policies:
• I ship worldwide from the UK
• Rough guide after production time: 
UK: 3 business days, US: 7-12 business days, Europe: 5-12 business days

• Please be aware if ordering from abroad, customs can add weeks onto the delivery time if they do decide to hold the package. This is completely out of my control and the majority of orders are not affected by this. Also, any taxes and customs charges occurred when shipping abroad are the responsibility of the buyer to pay.
• IT IS YOUR RESPONSIBILITY TO ENSURE YOUR ADDRESS IS CORRECT HERE ON ETSY WHEN YOU ORDER - We post to the exact address attached with the order so will not be held responsible for shipping to a misspelled or incorrect address
► Safety:
• Please do not give our products to children under 3 years old due to the risk of small parts. All little ones should be supervised whilst around or wearing any pieces.
► Packaging:
• Each item comes in a small organza bag and is posted out via Royal Mail in a protected, padded envelope to ensure its safe arrival.
► Care:
• Our jewellery whilst lightly splashproof is not waterproof and therefore should not be worn near any water at all to ensure you can wear it for as long as possible
• Remove when sleeping, showering, exercising, swimming or doing other physically strenuous activities to make your jewellery last longer
